article.description:
Dirk Nowitzki scored 24 points, and Michael Finley
added 13 to surpass 10,000 for his career as the Dallas Mavericks completed a four-game season series sweep of the Memphis Grizzlies with a 111-100 victory Saturday night.
article.headline: Finley scores 10,000th point in Mavs' win
article.linkText: Finley hits milestone as Mavs sweep Grizzlies
article.story:
DALLAS (AP) -- After games against the Los Angeles Lakers and San Antonio Spurs, the Dallas Mavericks feared a letdown against the Memphis Grizzlies.
Finley

It didn't happen. The Mavericks took care of the Grizzlies, the Western Conference's last-place team, with a 111-100 victory Saturday night. "They are a team that's really not going anywhere," Mavericks reserve guard Avery Johnson said. "It's tough, especially coming off a tough loss to the Spurs. So I commend our guys. We got it over after three quarters." Dirk Nowitzki scored 24 points, and Michael Finley added 13 to surpass 10,000 for his career as the Mavericks completed a four-game season series sweep of the Grizzlies. Finley became the 238th NBA player to reach 10,000 points with an 18-foot jumper in the final minute of the first quarter. The sellout crowd gave Finley a standing ovation after the milestone was announced. "I'm thankful that I did it at home," Finley said. "The Dallas fans have been real good for me, so to share it with them was special." Wang Zhizhi had a career-high 18 points, and Steve Nash scored 13 points for the Mavericks, who've won eight of 11 overall and 10 of 11 meetings against the Grizzlies. Wang hit all four 3-point attempts and went 7-for-9 from the field in his best game since arriving from China last season. "When he gets hot, that's when he's most effective for us," Nash said. "He made some shots, and that was good to see." Mavericks coach Don Nelson was able to rest his starters in the second half. All 11 Dallas players who got into the game scored, with the reserves contributing 47 points. "A lot of guys who normally don't get much playing time got a chance to get some minutes tonight," said Johnson, the team's No. 3 point guard who played 21 minutes. "It was good to get the starters some rest." Pau Gasol's 23 points and Stromile Swift's 20 paced the Grizzlies, who've lost six straight and are 2-15 in their last 17 games. "(The Mavericks) are good. They're a tough team to match up with," Grizzlies coach Sidney Lowe said. "They have so many weapons, people who can shoot the ball." The Mavericks took control in the first quarter and led 63-47 at halftime. In the first half, Nowitzki had 19 points and went 8-for-9 from the field. Dallas carried a 94-75 lead into the final quarter and led by as many as 23 in the fourth quarter as Nelson cleared his bench. Game notes
The Grizzlies' road record fell to 6-28. ... Dallas shot 60 percent from the field in the first half (24-for-40). ... Memphis guard Jason Williams was ejected with 4:10 left in the third quarter after earning his second technical foul. ... At 48-21, the Mavericks have their best record in club history after 69 games. ... Wang's previous career high was 15 points.
